<DOC><DOCNO> AP901020-0016 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-10-20-90 0047EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--PuertoRico-Drugs     10-20 0133</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Puerto Rico-Drugs,0136</SECOND><HEAD>Drugs Seized Off Puerto Rico</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   More than $15 million in cocaineand marijuana seized by U.S. officials have been taken to a navalbase along with 10 people arrested on drug charges, the U.S. CoastGuard said.   The drugs - 4,000 pounds of marijuana and 1,400 pounds ofcocaine - were discovered earlier this week in searches of twoships off Puerto Rico.   The U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration said the cocaine had astreet value of $12.7 million, and the marijuana was worth between$2.8 million and $4.8 million.   The drugs, the two unregistered vessels and 10 detained crewmencaptured off the coast Sunday and Monday were transported toRoosevelt Roads Naval Base on Puerto Rico on Friday, the CoastGuard said.</TEXT></DOC>